subSubSection.paragraph:
Compared with the other species that have antennae on a shelf, it has a granulate face and no distinct yellow marks along the inner orbits, the first flagellomere 2.3-2.5 times as long as wide, the areolet comparatively small, the first tergite 2.1 times as long as posteriorly wide, the second tergite 1.8 times as long as posteriorly wide. Additionally, the subocular sulcus is nearly straight, the POL 1.6 times as long as the diameter of a lateral ocellus, and the fore wing length is 2.4-2.8 mm (unlike in 

O. parvus

).

